article.headline: No. 23 Gonzaga 80, San Diego 58
article.story:
SPOKANE, Wash. --  Courtney Vandersloot scored 20 points and No. 23 Gonzaga rolled to an 80-58 victory over San Diego on Saturday, wrapping up the Bulldogs' second straight undefeated conference schedule.

The Bulldogs (26-4, 14-0 West Coast Conference) have won seven straight conference titles, and 30 consecutive regular-season league games dating to the 2009-09 season.

Katelan Redmon added 16 points, including a personal 8-0 run that gave Gonzaga a 42-24 lead in the first half, while Kayla Standish had 16 points and Janelle Bekkering 10.

Vandersloot and Bekkering were among five seniors honored in their final regular-season home game of the year. A sellout crowd of more than 6,000 showed up.

Sam Child scored 12 points to lead San Diego (15-13, 5-9).
